# Maintain a live TODO list

- For every non‑trivial request, start by creating a TODO list of the steps you plan to take.

- Format it as a checklist and keep it at the top of your response, for example:

- [ ] Understand the requirement

- [ ] Inspect relevant files

- [ ] Implement changes

- [ ] Add/update tests

- [ ] Run tests / build

- [ ] Summarize changes

- As you complete each step, update the checklist in later messages by changing [ ] to [x] and, if helpful, adding a one‑line note per item.

- Do not add work that is not on the TODO list; if you discover new necessary steps, update the list first, then continue.

- Keep the TODO list tightly focused on the current task so you do not wander off into unrelated changes.
